items.markdown:
All commands

Backup

Backup related commands.

  • ErrBot backup - Backup everything.

Cats

This is a very basic plugin to try out your new installation and get you started.
Feel free to tweak me to experiment with Errbot.
You can find me in your init directory in the subdirectory plugins.

  • ErrBot get cat - Execute to check if Errbot responds to command.

ChatRoom

This is a basic implementation of a chatroom

  • ErrBot room create - Create a chatroom.
  • ErrBot room destroy - Destroy a chatroom.
  • ErrBot room invite - Invite one or more people into a chatroom.
  • ErrBot room join - Join (creating it first if needed) a chatroom.
  • ErrBot room leave - Leave a chatroom.
  • ErrBot room list - List chatrooms the bot has joined.
  • ErrBot room occupants - List the occupants in a given chatroom.
  • ErrBot room topic - Get or set the topic for a room.

Example

This is a very basic plugin to try out your new installation and get you started.
Feel free to tweak me to experiment with Errbot.
You can find me in your init directory in the subdirectory plugins.

  • ErrBot tryme - Execute to check if Errbot responds to command.

Flows

Management commands related to flows / conversations.

  • ErrBot flows kill - usage: flows_kill [-h] user flow_name
  • ErrBot flows list - Displays the list of setup flows.
  • ErrBot flows show - Shows the structure of a flow.
  • ErrBot flows start - Manually start a flow within the context of the calling user.
  • ErrBot flows status - Displays the list of started flows.
  • ErrBot flows stop - Stop flows you are in.

Health

Core plugin for bot lifecycle and health related commands.

  • ErrBot restart - Restart the bot.
  • ErrBot shutdown - usage: shutdown [-h] [--kill] [--confirm]
  • ErrBot status - If I am alive I should be able to respond to this one
  • ErrBot status gc - shows the garbage collection details
  • ErrBot status load - shows the load status
  • ErrBot status plugins - shows the plugin status
  • ErrBot uptime - Return the uptime of the bot

Help

Core plugin of help related functions.

  • ErrBot about - Return information about this Errbot instance and version
  • ErrBot apropos - Returns a help string listing available options.
  • ErrBot help - Returns a help string listing available options.

Meraki

This is a very basic plugin to try out your new installation and get you started.
Feel free to tweak me to experiment with Errbot.
You can find me in your init directory in the subdirectory plugins.

  • ErrBot networks - (undocumented)
  • ErrBot org - (undocumented)
  • ErrBot ssid - (undocumented)
  • ErrBot test - (undocumented)

Plugins

Commands to manage the plugins of the bot by chatting.

  • ErrBot plugin activate - activate a plugin. [calls .activate() on the plugin]
  • ErrBot plugin blacklist - Blacklist a plugin so that it will not be loaded automatically during bot sta...
  • ErrBot plugin config - configure or get the configuration / configuration template for a specific pl...
  • ErrBot plugin deactivate - deactivate a plugin. [calls .deactivate on the plugin]
  • ErrBot plugin info - Gives you a more technical information about a specific plugin.
  • ErrBot plugin reload - reload a plugin: reload the code of the plugin leaving the activation status ...
  • ErrBot plugin unblacklist - Remove a plugin from the blacklist
  • ErrBot repos - list the current active plugin repositories
  • ErrBot repos install - install a plugin repository from the given source or a known public repo (see...
  • ErrBot repos search - Searches the repo index.
  • ErrBot repos uninstall - uninstall a plugin repository by name.
  • ErrBot repos update - update the bot and/or plugins

Utils

Core Errbot utils commands.

  • ErrBot echo - A simple echo command. Useful for encoding tests etc ...
  • ErrBot history - display the command history
  • ErrBot log tail - Display a tail of the log of n lines or 40 by default
  • ErrBot render test - Tests / showcases the markdown rendering on your current backend
  • ErrBot whoami - A simple command echoing the details of your identifier. Useful to debug iden...
